4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING PROPERTY TAXES FOR SENIOR CARE AND
5 HOUSING; PROVIDING A TEMPORARY TAX EXEMPTION FOR SENIOR CARE AND HOUSING
6 DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS; REQUIRING APPROVAL BY THE GOVERNING BODY OF A LOCAL
7 GOVERNMENT; PROVIDING FOR AN EXTENSION OF THE TAX EXEMPTION FOR CERTAIN PROPERTY;
8 PROVIDING FOR TERMINATION OF THE TAX EXEMPTION FOR CERTAIN EVENTS; PROVIDING
9 RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; AMENDING SECTION 15-10-305, MCA; AND
10 PROVIDING AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Short title. [Sections 1 through 8] may be cited as the "Senior Care
15 Facilities and Housing Development Exemption Act".
16
17 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Legislative purpose. The legislature finds and declares that there is a
18 shortage in this state of decent, safe, and sanitary, senior care and housing facilities that is affordable for all
19 seniors. To alleviate the high cost of facilities and housing for all seniors, the legislature believes it is essential
20 that property tax incentives be made available to tax-exempt organizations that assist senior Montanans in
21 meeting critical housing needs.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Definitions. As used in [sections 1 through 8], unless the context clearly
24 indicates otherwise, the following definitions apply:
25 (1) "Board" means the board of directors for a tax-exempt senior care and housing sponsor.
26 (2) “Department” means the department of revenue provided for in 2-15-1301.
27 (2) (a) "Local government" means the county, consolidated government, or incorporated city or
28 town where the senior development project is located or proposed to be located.
