2 to be located in an incorporated city or town.
3 (3) "Property owner-operator" means a corporation that is incorporated or admitted under a
4 certificate of authority under the laws of the state and that leases or purchases property for senior care facilities
5 and housing or related facilities, which may include a purchase from a tax-exempt senior care and housing
6 sponsor.
7 (4) "Senior care facilities" means some or all levels of a continuum of care. The term includes but
8 is not limited to independent living and housing, semi-independent living and housing, assisted living, in-home
9 nursing or assistant care, memory care, short-term or long-term medical care, or hospice.
10 (5) "Senior care facilities and housing" means senior care facilities and senior housing:
11 (a) specifically designed and operated to assist and benefit elderly persons;
12 (b) intended for, and solely occupied by, persons 62 years of age or older; or
13 (c) intended and operated for occupancy by at least one person 55 years of age or older in each
14 unit in accordance with the provisions of 42 U.S.C. 3607(b)(2)(C) and (b)(3) through (b)(5), as those provisions
15 read on March 31, 1996.
16 (6) (a) "Senior care and housing development project" means single-family homes and multifamily
17 projects for the primary purpose of acquiring land for, constructing, or rehabilitating accommodations for senior
18 care facilities and housing that may be retained and rented or sold to a property owner-operator for senior care
19 facilities and housing.
20 (b) The development process includes:
21 (i) the acquisition of property, not to exceed 250 acres;
22 (ii) the planning of the buildings, infrastructure, utilities, and improvements;
23 (iii) permitting;
24 (iv) the demolition of existing structures; and
25 (v) the construction, reconstruction, alteration, and repair of the improvements.
26 (7) "Tax-exempt senior care and housing sponsor" means a charitable nonprofit corporation that is
27 exempt from taxation under 26 U.S.C. 501(c)(3), as amended, and incorporated or admitted under a certificate
28 of authority under the Montana Nonprofit Corporation Act as provided in Title 35, chapter 2, and whose articles
