4 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Projects subject to existing development laws -- preference for
5 senior care facilities and housing authorized. (1) A senior care and housing development project is subject
6 to the planning, zoning, sanitary, and building laws, ordinances, and regulations applicable to the locality in
7 which the housing project is situated.
8 (2) A property OWNER-OPERATOR or tax-exempt senior care and housing sponsor shall extend
9 preference in occupancy for senior care facilities and housing.
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Temporary exemption for senior care and housing development
12 project -- rulemaking. (1) If the governing body approves a petition for a senior care and housing development
13 project pursuant to [section 4], the board of the tax-exempt senior care and housing sponsor may submit a
14 property tax exemption application to the department. The application must include the petition that was
15 submitted to the governing body and the resolution approving the petition. After the department has approved
16 the exemption application, the property of the senior care and housing development project is temporarily
17 exempt from all property taxation at the start of the property tax year beginning January 1 after the approval.
18 (2) At the time the exemption is granted, the department shall provide a notice to the clerk and
19 recorder in the county where the property is located, and the clerk shall file the notice. The notice must indicate
20 that an exemption pursuant to this section has been granted on a form prescribed by the department.
21 (3) Subject to subsection (5), the temporary exemption applies to all real property owned by a
22 property owner-operator or a tax-exempt senior care and housing sponsor within the senior care and housing
23 development project, including new construction, for a period equal to the lesser of 5 years or until the
24 development is final and operational. A tax-exempt property owner-operator or tax-exempt senior care and
25 housing sponsor may rent homes and multifamily projects for senior care facilities and housing without loss of
26 the temporary exemption.
27 (4) During the year in which the exemption provided for in subsection (3) expires, a tax-exempt
28 property owner-operator or the board of a tax-exempt senior care and housing sponsor may submit a renewal
